This paper discusses neural architectures for reading comprehension, which is a natural language processing task, suggesting that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the representation of semantic properties and entities, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The experiments conducted in the paper involve evaluating the hidden state vectors of neural readers, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. The paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category, as it deals with neural architectures. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category, as it deals with the representation of entities.
